<abstract abstract-type="short" xml:lang="en"><p><![CDATA[Abstract This article recalls Mariza Corrêa&#8217;s first steps in anthropology, and the production of her innovative master&#8217;s dissertation and the impact that it had on feminist politics in Brazil. It also addresses the importance of personal relations in academic production, with special consideration to Mariza Corrêa&#8217;s husband, Plínio Dentzien.]]></p></abstract>
